  "course_description": "Introduction to the American Legal System delves into the sources and structures shaping law in the United States. During the course, students will explore the four primary sources of law that shape the legal landscape in the United States: the U.S. Constitution, statutes, case (common) law, and administrative law. Students will also examine how federalism has shaped the U.S. legal system and will become familiar with the structure and interactions of courts in the U.S. legal system.",
